        <section><title>PoD at GSI (Grid Engine)</title>
            <para>
                For GSI users, who want to use PoD with our new SGE cluster. You need to build a source package of PoD using the following environment.
            </para>
<screen>
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$SGE_ROOT/lib/$SGE_ARCH/:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
export PATH=/misc/manafov/cmake/cmake_64bit/cmake/bin:$PATH
export PATH=/misc/manafov/Qt/4.4.2_lenny64/bin:$PATH
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/misc/manafov/Qt/4.4.2_lenny64/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
</screen>
        </section>
        
        <section><title>PoD at GSI (LSF)</title>
            <para>
                Users at GSI can install PoD from a source package or they can use a central installation of PoD.
                To enable a central installation the following command must be issued. The command will
                setup the environment for PoD and enable a given version (new, pro, or old).
            </para>
<screen>
<command>source pod_setup <replaceable>new|pro|old</replaceable></command>
</screen>
        </section>
        
        <section><title>PoD at CERN's AFS</title>
            <para>
                PoD has been tested and is used at CERN (with LSF, SGE, SSH plug-ins). The following environment settings could help to build PoD from the source in a CERN AFS directory on lxplus.cern.ch.
<screen>
# GCC
. /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/contrib/gcc/4.3/x86_64-slc5/setup.sh
# ROOT (you can use your version)
. /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/app/releases/ROOT/5.27.06/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/root/bin/thisroot.sh
# Qt
export PATH=/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/external/qt/4.4.2/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/bin:$PATH
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/external/qt/4.4.2/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
</screen>
            </para>
            <para>
                Since AFS doesn't support pipes you need to change PoD server working directory in the user defaults configuration.
                <ulink url="http://www-linux.gsi.de/%7Emanafov/D-Grid/docz/PoD/html/html_help/Known_Issues.html#PoDonAFS">Find out more on this.</ulink>
            </para>
        </section>
